@startuml reboot-reflash
title REBOOT — remote reset & cable-free Pico W reflashing
hide footbox
skinparam shadowing false

actor "Operator" as O
participant "Coordinator\n(wasp_client.py)" as C
participant "Node" as N

== Plain reboot (any board): mode 0 ==

O -> C : wasp_client.py <ip> reboot
C -> N : REBOOT [mode = 0]
N --> C : RESULT (empty ack)\n**acked first** — then reboot ~500 ms later
N -> N : sys_reboot(COLD)
...node boots, joins the network, DHCP...
N ->> C : ANNOUNCE resumes (UDP :4243)

== Reflash without touching BOOTSEL (RP2040 only): mode 1 ==

O -> C : wasp_client.py <ip> reboot --bootsel
C -> N : REBOOT [mode = 1]
N --> C : RESULT (empty ack)
N -> N : reset_usb_boot(0, 0)\n→ ROM USB bootloader
note over N : the **RPI-RP2** mass-storage drive\nenumerates on the USB host
O -> N : cp build/pico/zephyr/zephyr.uf2\n   /media/$USER/RPI-RP2/
N -> N : flashes itself, reboots\ninto the new firmware
...~20 s...
N ->> C : ANNOUNCE (new firmware online)
note right of O : the BOOTSEL-button dance is only\nneeded for the very first flash\n(or a bricked board)

== mode 1 on a board with no USB bootloader ==

C -> N : REBOOT [mode = 1] (e.g. the Nucleo)
N --> C : ERROR [UNSUPPORTED,\n"no bootloader entry on this SoC"]
note right of C : the node does **not** reboot —\nuse mode 0 and west flash instead
@enduml
